                <div class="faq-answer">Yes, reputable budgeting apps are generally safe. They use bank-level encryption (often 256-bit AES) and rely on secure third-party aggregators like Plaid or Finicity to connect to your accounts. They have read-only access, meaning they cannot move money or make changes to your accounts.</div>
            </div>
            <div class="faq-item">
                <button class="faq-question" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">Can I share a budgeting app with my partner?</button>
                <div class="faq-answer">Many top budgeting apps offer family sharing or partner features. YNAB allows you to share your subscription with up to five people, Monarch Money includes a partner invite feature, and Goodbudget is designed for couples sharing a single account.</div>
            </div>
            <div class="faq-item">
