                <div class="faq-answer">Not necessarily. There are excellent free options available, such as the free tier of EveryDollar or Goodbudget. However, premium apps or paid tiers usually offer advanced features like automatic bank syncing, investment tracking, and detailed reporting, which many users find worth the cost.</div>
            </div>
            <div class="faq-item">
                <button class="faq-question" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">What is the best alternative to Mint?</button>
                <div class="faq-answer">Since Mint shut down, many users have migrated to Monarch Money, Simplifi by Quicken, or Copilot. These apps offer robust alternatives with comprehensive dashboards, automatic syncing, and modern interfaces that often surpass what Mint offered.</div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </main>
</div>

  <script is:inline type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify(faqSchema)} />

